snippet.textDisplay: Indeed, by the grace of God, we will get through this pandemic, but I don't things will ever be the same in our country. Most folks will be hesitant about big gatherings, standing room only concerts, elbow to elbow crowds. Some employers will not be able to bring everyone back to work in their companies, probably reducing their staff levels permanently. Some restaurants, already marginally profitable and in debt, will go to Chapter 7, or close. There will be economic casualties in this war, winners, mostly losers. We will all have to review our spending habits, learn to be smart, practice frugality, hold back money for a rainy day, take care of our health. We will probably never shake hands again at church, maybe avoid hugging. Most of all, we have to renew our faith in God, remembering life can be uncertain, walk in wisdom.
snippet.textOriginal: Indeed, by the grace of God, we will get through this pandemic, but I don't things will ever be the same in our country.
